    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-03-02T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-03-02T18:00:00-05:00" n="129"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d129">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.5 <gloss target="#t_MAP1">MAP</gloss>/3–250:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in the United Kingdom</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d129fn1">This telegram was drafted by William N. Fraleigh of
                        the Office of European Regional Affairs, Bureau of European Affairs, and was
                        concurred in by H. F. Arthur Schoenfeld of the Mutual Defense Assistance
                        Program. This telegram was repeated to the missions in Rome, Paris,
                        Brussels, The Hague, Oslo, Copenhagen, Luxembourg, Frankfort, and
                        Heidelberg.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-03-02T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 2, 1950—6 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>955. Att <gloss target="#t_ECC1">ECC</gloss>. Urtel 900 Feb 16.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d129fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_269">p. 269</ref>.</note>
                    Opinion here agrees with you that vigorous counteraction by non-Commie labor
                    major element for producing Commie defeat in expected arms shipment strikes and
                    considers <gloss target="#t_ITF1">ITF</gloss> potentially most important
                    internatl labor body in this <pb facs="0289" n="273" xml:id="pg_273"/>
                    connection. Dept notes with special interest actions and statements by European
                    non-Commies, such as vote of Ital seamen and portworkers favoring unloading
                    described Rome tel 598, Feb 14.<note n="3" xml:id="d129fn3">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>While fol policy of no direct US Govt intervention in arms strike question Dept
                    has been discreetly in touch with <gloss target="#t_AFL1">AFL</gloss> and <gloss
                        target="#t_CIO1">CIO</gloss> and finds full weight of Amer labor support
                    being given publicly to <gloss target="#t_MDAP1">MDAP</gloss>. Curran<note n="4"
                        xml:id="d129fn4">Joseph E. Curran, President of the National Maritime Union,
                        affiliated with the Congress of Industrial Organizations.</note> Pres.
                        <gloss target="#t_CIO1">CIO</gloss> Maritime Union and Ryan<note n="5"
                        xml:id="d129fn5">Joseph P. Ryan, President of the International
                        Longshoremen’s Association, affiliated with the American Federation of
                        Labor.</note> Pres. <gloss target="#t_AFL1">AFL</gloss> longshoremen’s Assoc
                    have issued statements supporting <gloss target="#t_MDAP1">MDAP</gloss>. <gloss
                        target="#t_CIO1">CIO</gloss> Exec Board last week reaffirmed support of
                        <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NAT</gloss>. Green <gloss target="#t_AFL1"
                        >AFL</gloss> will make supporting statement at time he considers
                    appropriate. Similar statements may be expected from other labor leaders.
                        Lyon,<note n="6" xml:id="d129fn6">Arlon E. Lyon, member of the Executive
                        Committee, International Transport Workers’ Federation.</note> US member
                        <gloss target="#t_ITF1">ITF</gloss> Exec, states he is actively engaged in
                    raising funds from labor sources for <gloss target="#t_ITF1">ITF</gloss>
                    Vigilance Comite activities.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
